TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Social Discount Rate
AU  - Caplin, Andrew
AU  - Leahy, John
Y1  - 2004/12/01
PY  - 2004
DA  - 2004/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/424740
DO  - 10.1086/424740
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 1257
EP  - 1268
VL  - 112
IS  - 6
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - What discount rate should be applied to social investments? It is standard to use the market interest rate, thereby respecting private preferences. We show that application of this ?revealed preference? criterion rests on faith, not on logic. It is justified only if preferences over all choices, including past choices, are time invariant. The conditions for this to be true are stringent. Under more reasonable conditions, policy makers should be more patient than private citizens, whose choices define the most short?sighted Pareto optimum.
AB  - What discount rate should be applied to social investments? It is standard to use the market interest rate, thereby respecting private preferences. We show that application of this ?revealed preference? criterion rests on faith, not on logic. It is justified only if preferences over all choices, including past choices, are time invariant. The conditions for this to be true are stringent. Under more reasonable conditions, policy makers should be more patient than private citizens, whose choices define the most short?sighted Pareto optimum.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/424740
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/424740
Y2  - 2024/03/19
